{
  "texts": [
    "This section has outlined the possible privacy infringements of IXR, expanding beyond the traditional notion of privacy as data protection-although biometric data privacy is a major concern in IXR-to consider decisional and local privacy.",
    "IXR opens new avenues for surveillance and persuasion, in the physical and virtual worlds, and our recommendations for addressing them are in Sect. 7.",
    "Existing EU legislation may mitigate some of the safety and privacy concerns outlined above.",
    "We consider the applicability to IXR of six areas of relevant legislation.",
    "While other areas of sectoral legislation may apply to specific IXR applications, we focus here on more broadly pertinent legislation based on our analysis of the specific risks inherent to IXR."
  ]
}